    "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India",
    "title": "India",
    "content": "India is a federal union comprising 28 states and 8 union territories. It is characterized by immense geographical and climatic diversity, ranging from the Himalayan peaks in the north to tropical coastlines. The nation has a rich, complex history spanning millennia, marked by the rise and fall of various empires and significant cultural contributions. Modern India emerged from British colonial rule in 1947 and has since developed into a major global economic and political power, known for its diverse linguistic landscape, vibrant cultural traditions, and significant advancements in science and technology. Its economy is one of the fastest-growing in the world.",
    "snippet": "India, officially the Republic of India, is a country in South Asia. It is the seventh-largest country by area, the second-most populous country, and the most populous democracy in the world. India shares land borders with Pakistan to the west; China, Nepal, and Bhutan to the north; and Bangladesh and Myanmar to the east.",
    "created_at": "2026-01-20T18:16:00.985919Z",
