    "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Asia",
    "title": "South Asia",
    "content": "South Asia is a geographically and culturally diverse region in the southern part of Asia, encompassing a significant portion of the Indian subcontinent. It is characterized by high population density and rapid economic growth in several nations, though it also faces considerable challenges related to poverty and development. The region's history is marked by ancient civilizations, colonial rule, and the subsequent partition of British India, which heavily influenced the modern political map. Key features include the Himalayas in the north, the Indo-Gangetic Plain, and extensive coastlines, supporting diverse climates and ecosystems. Major religions originating here include Hinduism, Buddhism, Jainism, and Sikhism.",
    "snippet": "South Asia is a region in the southern region of the Asian continent. It generally includes the countries of India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Nepal, Bhutan, and the Maldives. The region is home to nearly two billion people, making it the most populous region in the world.",
    "created_at": "2026-01-20T18:52:36.067418Z",
